Niger State Governor, Abubakar Sani Bello has described the leadership style of the Senate President, Ahmad Ibrahim Lawan as impressive. Bello said this in a message to felicitate the President of the Senate on his 63rd birthday in Minna. He described Lawan as a renowned educationist, progressive legislator and a good leader who is contributing his quota to the development of the country. Atiku, Ayu, Mark, Lawan, Nnamani Mourn Joseph Wayas Lawan Launches 120-bed Capacity Mother, Child Hospital In Gashua Bello claimed the celebrant’s good leadership qualities are not in doubt as is evident in the way he pilots the affairs of the upper legislative Chamber. He said the Senate President has been consistent in championing the enactment of laws and oversight functions that will engender rapid growth and development of the Nation. “I want to join millions of your well-wishers to thank Allah for adding another year to your years. You have made so much impact on the development of Democracy in this country. “Your leadership style in the Senate is an impressive one,” he said. Bello then prayed Allah to continue to guide and protect the Lawan, give him more strength and wisdom as well as good health to continue to provide the right leadership that would strengthen the nation’s democracy.